## Final governance‑ready paragraph (Risk Committee / Fed / Model Validation)

This AI‑led equity stress scenario set calibrates **Moderate** and **Severe** outcomes for SPX and QQQ using an explicit decomposition ( \Delta\ln(P)=\Delta\ln(EPS)+\Delta\ln(P/E)+\Delta P_{\text{contagion}} ) with duration‑based valuation attribution ( \Delta\ln(P/E)\approx -D_{\text{eq}}(\Delta r+\Delta ERP-\Delta g) ). The design enforces horizon discipline: **ERP/multiples/contagion reprice over weeks to months**, while **EPS and long‑run growth expectations reset over 2–4 quarters**. Numerical anchors are empirical: Q4‑2018 provides the fast correction magnitude (S&P 500 **−19.8%**) and tech drawdown feasibility (Nasdaq‑100 **−23%** at the Dec‑24 nadir), 2022 provides valuation compression evidence (Nasdaq‑100 trailing P/E **24.8** on May‑20 and late‑2020 peak **just under 40**), and implied ERP regime shifts from Damodaran support +80 bps (orderly) and ~+180 bps (disorderly) step‑ups. ([Los Angeles Times][1]) Severe adds non‑linear mechanisms absent from Moderate—**forced deleveraging, dispersion collapse, and near‑unity correlation**—rather than scaling magnitudes linearly, with cross‑asset coherence enforced (ERP↑, vol↑, correlation↑). ([CME Group][4])

